    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-08-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-08-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="165"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d165">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Egan</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-08-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 27, 1891</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Egan telegraphs that the revolutionists were victorious in a fierce battle
                    near Valparaiso last Friday and that a decisive engagement was expected on the
                    day of the sending of his telegram. He states that there is no communication
                    between Valparaiso and Santiago and says it is <pb facs="0261" n="155"
                        xml:id="pg_155"/> very important that he be informed by telegraph of any
                    early reliable news which the Department might receive. Thinks it may be
                    possible to stop further bloodshed.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
